caption: Very disappointing restaurant. Excessively priced restaurant with sub par food. I would not waste your time or money. Huge disappointment from start to finish.

My mom sent me a one of their gift boxes, and it was just the taste of home I needed!  All of the items were absolutely delicious and for me, it was the perfect selection of things to supplement my kitchen; great quality and variety.  I undoubtedly will enjoy this for weeks!

Our children sent us a gift box for the holidays. Everything was amazing! I loved the treasure hunt in the box — I kept finding more and more treasures. The chocolate and orange biscotti were incredible—the best we’ve ever eaten. And the pasta and tomatoes were great. They made for a lovely New Year’s Eve dinner. Aldo’s was our favorite Little Italy restaurant when we lived in HoCo before we moved down to Florida. It was wonderful to receive such delicious  treats from them. Can’t wait to visit them again in 2021 on our next visit to Baltimore when Covid passes. Grazie mille, Aldo’s!
Highly recommend. They have amazing house made pasta.
Sergio pours his heart and soul into this restaurant and it shows. Consistently amazing food every time I dine here !!

I made reservations for my boyfriend's bday based on reviews. The evening was perfect! Food, wine, ambience, and service could not have been better. Aldo personally came to the table to greet us and share the house made lemoncello...we ended up leaving with an entire bottle. We'll definitely return for round two.
We love Aldos and always choose it when dining in Little Italy.

I rarely write a review for any reastaurant. But Aldo's is so consistently good I would recommend this place to everyone.  The prices are on the higher side but once you taste the food you will not be disappointed. We usually go when the place first opens  at 5 o'clock.  Service and food is alway better when they are not too crowded. But then again, they are never too crowded considering our current circumstances. Have been here at least 20 rimes and have never been disappointed.

I went to Aldo's after a friend recommended the restaurant as "the best Italian food in Little Italy." I was not disappointed.  Oh. My. Goodness. Absolutely amazing service, delicious food and a homemade limoncello to die for. I loved every minute of the entire experience. Highly recommend for anyone looking for wonderful food and a welcoming team that makes you feel like family.
Excellent food and service.  The food here is delicious and the service is amazing.
The food and service were excellent!  I definitely will be back in the future!

Called ahead and reserved a table for me and my bf. Was warmly greeted by the hostess. Upon arrival , our server was stuffy and pretentious , we ordered a wine they were out. We watched him walk past us 3 times , circle back , greet and take an order from a new table. Come back with the new tables wine completely ignoring us. Not sure if it was because I’m a tan , non Anglo Saxon , mixed woman , and my bf is Hispanic and mixed as well , but the vibes were all off. It’s a shame things like this continue in little Italy. We went across the street to chipparellis , were instantly greeted with bread and water, and had our wine on the table in the time it took us to wait and leave aldos unattended to. Save your money people !

Rude, stuffy yet somehow also completely inadequate service. Ordered wine, out of stock. Order another wine. Watched our server walk to 3 other tables, collecting a wine and food order before returning with this other tables' wine. This other table that sat and ordered after we did. On a  slow Tuesday night.

Our server, Joe B, was a delight. The food was beyond expectation, when we already had high expectations. Bolognese, saltimbocca, and escargot followed up with a cleanse of limoncello was simply perfect.

This restaurant was always our go-to for super special occasions. Today I ordered carryout since I totally dropped the ball for my husband's birthday (that he had to remind me about). I ordered the rigatoni alla vodka (for my 9 year old), orechiette for me, and fettuccini and lobster for my husband. I also ordered a caesar salad, the beet salad, meatballs and garlic bread. For dessert, I ordered a cannoli and the chocolate mousse. I didn't realize how big the caesar would be. We will be eating the beet salad another day as the caesar was enough for all 3 of us. Really loved the tang of the dressing. Can't stand when the dressing is super heavy. Everyone really loved their dishes and we each had a meatball. They give you a ton of food. My husband ate all of his (didn't even share!) and our son and I both have food left over. The mousse is really rich so I recommend having a glass of milk (what my son did) or chai tea (what I did) with it. It was so decadent! The cannoli was really good too. Had to steal it away from my husband so my son and I could take a bite. I also bought a bottle of chianti and the housemade limoncello. It was a dry chianti recommended by the bartender since the one I initially ordered was sold out. We didn't really drink the limoncello because there were so many other flavors with the meal so that will have to wait for another day. The wine was well received.  It was super easy to order over the phone. I was able to choose a time for pick up. Though I'm not quite comfortable with eating indoors yet, I do love ordering from my favorite restaurants! They were super friendly and helpful over the phone and in person. I will definitely order from them again.
Always great food, wine and people! THE best Italian restaurant in Maryland
Best restaurant in Baltimore. If you're looking for excellent service and food, look no further. Every time I visit, I am amazed.

Went here alone during a business trip and was blown away by the service and treatment by the staff. The owner Sergio also came out of the kitchen to talk and was a wonderful host. As for the food, I had fried calamari and chicken Marsala. Both were terrific and you could tell everything was fresh and the highest quality. The Marsala sauce and tenderness of the chicken are in my memory forever! For dessert, I had the cannoli.....sublime, not too sweet...perfect. If you go, you will leave satisfied!

I have never written a review for a restaurant, but I felt that this restaurant had to be commended. As soon as my friend and I walked into the restaurant, we were warmly welcomed with true sincerity. Our servers Eugene, and server in training, Joe, were attentive, sociable, and knowledgable while guiding us through the courses. The food was "buonissimo," without the need for improvement! The complimentary plates and drinks from the owner were delightfully unexpected and gratefully consumed. While the food (especially the meatballs and limoncello) were amazing, the experience of the dinner really left a favorable impression. My only suggestion is that the wine could be more reasonably priced.
Great food and service. Has become a favorite

We had a wonderful meal and a romantic evening celebrating our 35th wedding anniversary at  Aldo’s.  Charming ambiance, excellent service and delicious food.  This was not the first time, nor will it be the last!  Magnifico!
There for a conference. Food was above average. The restaurant is not best equipped for large parties.
Excellent service, food, and ambiance... will go there again on special occasions!

The Filet Mignon was outstanding.  Our party of 4 enjoyed everything we ordered.  Will recommend but bring your wallet, it is expensive.  Friendly staff who kept a smile on our faces.  Note:. When making reservations with any restaurant, ask them if the on-line menu represents their current menu so you will not be disappointed.

My best friend and I went to Aldo's Ristorante on 02/15/2020. We walked in and the staff was so welcoming, the atmosphere was incredibly warm and inviting too. We had reservations, so there was no wait. The host directed us to wait for a minute to be sat at our table, while that was happening the nice gentleman at the coat check, checked our coats and then we were seated! (So super fancy)  I don't drink, so I started with a sparkling water, and a surprise to me I was served the whole bottle throughout the night, it was refreshing. My best friend got distilled water and a glass of red wine, she said it was incredible! We started with the Calamari with a side of the most tasteful, beautiful, red marinara sauce to dip the Calamari in. The Calamari was cooked to the upmost perfection, melted in my mouth and was not over fried. We crushed the ENTIRE appetizer, in what felt like seconds, I was saddened when we finished eating it all. Moving on to the main course, I ordered the Fettuccine, Sous-Vide Petite Cold Water Lobster Tail, in a Cognac Tomato-Cream Sauce. Now, when I tell you the presentation alone was amazing, when I took the first bite of Lobster with the fettuccine and cream sauce it was a whirl wind of flavors, and euphoria in my mouth. The sauce was creamy beyond words and everything flowed together so well. I am not exaggerating when I say, this was the BEST pasta dish I have ever put into my mouth. I only had leftovers, because obviously we were at an Italian restaurant and needed to try the dessert! We ended the evening with an Apple Tart with Vanilla Gelato. It was served warm, the outer crust was so crispy and delicious, the apples were perfectly soft and the mixture with the vanilla gelato was to die for, I could've eaten 5 of them, but I am 30 now and I have to be responsible (haha) My best friend also ordered a cup of coffee, black, two sugars, I tried it and wanted to drink the whole pot. I am not a fan of hot black coffee, but Aldo's Ristorante made me a fan, and I could drink a pot of that pure black perfection they call coffee everyday of my life. Hands down the best experience and I beg everyone in the ENTIRE state of Maryland, Country, and the entire world basically to try this amazing five star restaurant. YOU WILL NOT BE DISAPPOINTED! **Chef's kiss**
Delicious carbonara. Great service!

Please, please go visit Aldo's. Not only is there food delicious the service that you receive there will go way beyond your expectations. The space is very unique and you will leave having had your very own memorable experience!!
The food is good and the waiters are nice but it's overrated. The place is beautiful and romantic.

If you  are not eating Italian food at Aldos I don’t know what it is that you are doing with your life. Stop, go, you will be planning a return visit after your first bite! It’s an institution not a restaurant! Ciao!

Definitely the best Italian (if not the best overall) in Baltimore. No competition. From the intimate yet airy atmosphere to the impeccable service, Aldo's is always guaranteed to be a memorable night out. I send all my Airbnb guests here for a special dinner and it never fails to impress!  But let's talk about the food.  First- the sauces. Sergio and Aldo have the magic touch when it comes to sauces. Each one a little different. Each one more delicious than the last.  For an appetizer I had the meatballs in a red sauce with whipped burrata. Possibly the best meatballs this Jersey girl has ever had.  But that sauce was like heaven on a spoon.  My brother had the tuna tartare- also amazing. Perfect amount of perfectly seasoned tuna on a crunchy shell with the right mix of sweet and salty. Delicious.  For dinner my dad had the chicken marsala which was some of the best marsala I recall tasting. I had the steak with an onion wine sauce. Cooked perfectly med rare and nicely set off with greens in a vinegarette. The perfect spicy complement to the slightly sweet sauce in the steak.  We added a side of the homemade pappardelle with the wild boar ragu. Always one of my fave dishes. And it didn't disappoint.  I wish I could remember her name, but the lady who waited on us (recently back from maternity leave) was delightful and charming. And did a terrific job of ensuring we had an amazing experience!  I was so enthralled with the food I forgot to take pictures.  Next time!
Food was delicious and the service was amazing!
Great

Second time we've done a New Years Eve here - and it never disappoints! The prix fixe menu is well thought out and has something for everyone, including a champagne toast at the end! As they have printed on their menus, they were doing farm to table before that was a hot term for a new restaurant. The staff is always amazing and makes you feel so special as soon as you walk through the door. And above all - get the wild boar ragu. Heck, order a second helping to take home - its amazing!
Love this place!
No complaints. The food was very good. The crab cake and sirloin had great taste. The crab cake had no filler.
Great food!
The food was delicious but our server was a little slow but very nice
Hands down the finest Italian cuisine Baltimore has to offer.

My significant other and I had dinner here for our anniversary yesterday. The restaurant itself is very warm and welcoming, and in my opinion captivates true classic Italian. The food was delicious, as were the drinks, but the thing that stuck out to me the most was the exemplary customer service. From the moment we entered the establishment until we left I was very comfortable with the way that we were treated. No, we aren't Italian, but I would definitely go back!

If you want to treat yourself to spectacular Italian food this is the place to go. There are a variety of seating places available. This place is very expensive, most everything comes a la carte, but it is well worth it if you can afford it.
Service, drink and food was excellent.
Every dish was incredible. We're definitely returning very soon!
Unbelievable great food! Everything from the setting to the service to the most amazing food!
Delicious, upscale Italian cuisine. Service is fantastic. Note that the valet parking service operates for the whole block, not just Aldo's.

Amazing service, food was off the chain ! Deliciously good , prepared and cooked to perfection! Definitely would recommend and yes , going back ! PERFECT ANNIVERSARY DINNER ! Elegant atmosphere,  server,  host , Bon appetit!
Love the food and great friendly service!
It's the epitome of elegance

Aldo's is a must when I'm in Baltimore! Love the surroundings and the food is out if this world.  It's in the Little Italy section which is a must see any way. So get to Little Italy area and head to Aldo's!
Exceptional food and service!
Excellent food and great service!

Aldo’s is very uniquely authentic Italian food worth trying. Do your taste buds a favor! If you are with a group I suggest ordering meals to share because there are too many delicious meals to pick from. Our group did this and glad I got to sample multiple culinary delights. Can’t wait to visit Baltimore again. By the way save room for desert you have never tasted cannoli and Tiramisu as good as this!
Homemade Pasta Trio!!  Bring your best & non-judgmental friend (minimum of 2 people per order) and eat your way to pasta heaven.  Rigatoni alla Vodka • Orecchiette Pasta • Rigatoni Bolognese 🖤
Always good! Try the wild boar ragu!
Great food, great service, great bar service too! Miserable valet parking service

Aldo’s was a wonderful experience. The food melted in our mouth. Fresh ingredients with lots of bold flavors and true authentic Italian cuisine.  The service was impeccable and atmosphere was very pleasant. Our waiter Brian was very efficient and kept a close eye on us at all times to make sure everything was ok. I can’t wait for my husband and I to go back again!
(Translated by Google) Taste the best  (Original) 맛 최고

Aldo's will exceed your expectations on both a culinary and service level.  As an event planner, I was looking for a space for 30+ people on the night before Preakness.  This is one of the busiest nights of the entire year in Baltimore as the city is sold out on hotels and restaurants are packed.  From the initial contact to the final bill, everything was perfect.  They were accommodating to let us choose a menu to service the needs of the large group.  We were not forced to choose off a pre-planned menu.  They made sure the specialty wine the client wanted was in stock in sufficient quantities.  The food was delicious!  Shrimp scampi, antipasta, many veal dishes including the osso bucco and of course the pastas!  If you don't have their carbonara, you have missed one of life's great pleasures.  It's a tough call between that and the Bolognese, you can't go wrong.  Sergio, Margaret and the entire staff knocked it out of the park!
Incredible experience!  Third motto, if we have the ingredients,  we don't say no.

Been in Baltimore for a few days with my girlfriend and daughter and hadn't been to impressed with the food after a few high-end dinners. But then we found Aldo's. Unbelievable food, atmosphere, and the service was top notch. We had shrimp scampi, pasta carbonara and burrata rigitoni. Everything was perfectly seasoned. Can't wait to go back.
Fantastic!! Great food, Great people

I could have sworn I left a review. Maybe I had on Facebook.  I used to work the valet in little Italy and never had once stepped inside of Aldo’s. I guess it’s like the street urchin becomes the... I dono.  Anyways.  Very accommodating to the point that a rose under my request was added to my table for my girlfriend’s birthday.  Great service. Great food. Thank you.

Not great, maybe this was place was good at one time, but clearly is not interested in changing with the times. Everything was old a clunky and tired. Restaurant was not very clean, the paper towel basket in the ladies room had years if dust, and some "dirt" behind the door makes me wonder if there is a mouse problem here. Our waiter could not pronounce the specials. The cheese in my caprese was out of the refrigerator cold, not rich and creamy, my pasta was salty and oily. And when my husband ordered a martini with blue cheese olives I think they put salad dressing in regular olives...
One of the finest Italian restaurants I've ever patronized.  The osso bucco is the food of the Gods. Every time I go to Baltimore, I eat at Aldo's.

Fantastic ambience and food. Chef Sergio Vitale has curated an amazing menu of Southern Italian cuisine. Apps- try the shrimp scampi Salads- caprese or mista Pasta- all are amazing... try the gnocchi (off menu) Entrees- sane as above... all are amazing.  Personally I love the tournados Dessert- yes please!
Aldo's is fantastic. We love it there and their linguine and clams is the best around.
Incredibly good food and a perfect ambiance.  An amazing server helped us throughout the night.

Although I've been dining at Aldo's for MANY years, it didn't take more than a few visits for it to feel like home.  A family-owned restaurant, Aldo and his sons Sergio and Allesandro make everyone feel welcome, cared for and as an extension of their family.  And THE FOOD!!  So exquisite and cooked to perfection - every single time.  My mother spent a month in Italy and couldn't find a better meal.  If you haven't tried Aldo's yet, that really needs to change.
Great staff, delicious food, tasty wine. I look forward coming here every year during the holidays. All around great!
Best Restaurant in Baltimore!

I'm over 70 years old and I've eaten in a lot of restaurants all over the world this was the greatest Italian dinner that we have ever experienced. I would drive to Baltimore again just to go to go to ALDOS
Amazing restaurant! You MUST try the eggplant parm appetizer! Don't even like eggplant, and loved it! Best Ossobucco ever had!

Outstanding service, food and ambiance. In my 15 yrs of eating in this restaurant, I never had a meal I didn't like nor did I ever send one back. The Vitale Family are the most gracious restaurateurs you will ever meet. Do yourself a favor and visit this "Gem". Well done Aldo's
Cannot wait to go back to Aldos! I dream nightly of their delicious pasta gorgeous atmosphere and wonderful service! What they do is absolutely magic

Definitely the best place to have dinner in Little Italy and one of the best in Baltimore. The atmosphere of the place is very upscale which what I was looking for. Food was excellent and the service was very attentive and superb.
Awesome food and phenomenal service. Their  house made limoncello is the best. I've been their fan for 4 years now and they never disappoint!
Awesome food! Awesome service! Awesome family!
Aldo’s is a fine dining restaurant with a friendly wait staff superb food and some off the menu items that area can’t miss.
This is my go to place for many years. The service, hospitality and food is spot on. A visit for a glass of wine or a 5 course meal is always enjoyable.

Aldo’s has the best Italian food in the state of Maryland and the service is great too!!! The wine cellar is ideal for private dinners. I love the eggplant tower and the rigatoni bolognese. The white clam sauce is loaded with clams, more than I’ve ever seen at other restaurants. At the end of the meal, enjoy the homemade creamy limoncello made on the premises. You never know who you will see dining at Aldo’s.

Aldo’s is a gem in Little Italy. Father Aldo and son Sergio make you feel like your are a guest in their home. The preparations are authentic with an exacting attention to detail. The service is impeccable. Make sure you ask for a tour of the cellar. Aldo renovated the restaurant by hand. Great spot for celebrity sightings.

This year alone, at Aldo’s, I’ve had a romantic dinner, a family dinner, a dinner with an old college friend, a business dinner, and a large group dinner for 57 guests. At each dinner, the food and wine was amazing, and Aldo’s service was impeccable and perfectly tuned to the purpose of the evening. This is one of the best restaurants in Baltimore and the best Italian Ristorante in Maryland, and they’ve earned my return visits over and over again.

For the past twenty years, Aldos has been a standout in Baltimore and an always exceptional experience for scores of family and business dinners. From a customized Mother’s Day lunch, to a congratulatory business dinner, to a milestone dinner with old friends, to a heartwarming family ritual, Aldos has always been there for us. Aldo, Sergio, Robert, and Roman are mire like family or great friends than simply chefs, hosts or servers. Warm, attentive service, excellent food, and a great sense of custom, culture and tradition keeps us coming back.

Uhhhh...hit and miss on the food and subsequently not worth the high end prices. Very friendly and courteous staff and pleasant atmosphere as expected in a high end restaurant...but food was very disappointing. The shrimp bisque was salty and lacked and pleasant flavor (we normally love bisque soups) so my wife didnt eat it and after tasting it I passed on it too. The lobster on my fettuccine was so mushy that I was afraid to finish eating it...not sure what would cause lobster to be mushy like jello... but it wasnt normal. The actual fettuccini was good and my wife thought her crab cake was very good. Considering the pricey menu these type of results just make it a very poor choice.
Loved the food and the atmosphere!
I started off with sparkling water, my entree was linguine and clam sauce and I skipped on desert ..
The food here is delicious. Service is exceptional! Our host Mj was very welcoming and friendly. He made our experience enjoyable and pleasant. Will definitely be a returning customer.
incredible italian food, every item was amazing

I dined at Aldos solo at the bar for Restaurant week. I had dined there a few years ago for my birthday and loved the food and ambiance. It is pricey restaurant week is a great time to go to celebrate with someone special. Ate here for my wife's birthday. Food was outstanding and so was the overall service! The cocktails were good. Would definitely eat here again.

We were part of a private party in a small room. I don't know if that would affect the experience. The building is so (for lack of a better word) cool. Atmosphere = 10/10 The staff were helpful, attentive, and attempted to be discreet. (We might have been difficult.) Service = 10/10 There were 4 courses, all of which were amazing. I had Rigatoni Bolognese and it was delicious. So delicious that I am still telling people about it weeks later. I don't know what they do differently, but the food is incredible. Food = 11/10. Highly recommend.
Wonderful service and food is great.
Food was good. Service was ok.
The food was fantastic
Not the best experience but Sergio has gained my respect. Would love to give Aldo’s another try sometime.

Aldo's was fantastic. Our server Eugene was on point, great recommendations, and wonderful service. Ossobuco was out of this world and the rigatoni bolognese was great! Can't wait to go back and try more of the menu. Thank you for a wonderful first experience there.
Delicious food. Pricy but romantic. Service is excellent. The staff is well-informed of the menu.
Pricy but really nice food. Pasta trio very tasty.
Went here with my fiancé for Valentine’s Day dinner.  As expected they were very busy but the staff was super friendly and the food was excellent.  Great atmosphere and will definitely go back!

We went for a family birthday celebration. It was fantastic! We were in the wine cellar,which had great ambience! The food and service was wonderful & more. Thank you for making our celebration even more special.
Excellent Italian spot in Baltimore. Great atmosphere, service and food. Don't expect to eat and run, it's coordinated so that you spend quality time there and enjoy your evening. Kudos to the owner.

My boyfriend made reservations for Valentine’s Day weekend. Kind of strange that there was plenty of open tables on a Friday night. But I guess that’s a testimate to the service and food. I wouldn’t know because we left before the food came. I asked to substitute the spinach for another vegetable and the waiter had a confused look on his face. Wouldn’t reccommend. Awkward seating far away for couples.
Great service. Good food. Valet parking. What more could you ask for.

Food was just incredibly good. It took 30 minutes (with reservation and being on time) to sit us down at a table and the waiter automatically added a 20% tip on our bill. (I always tip 20% anyway). Are little details like those what will make us chose a different high end italian restaurant next time.
Best Italian restaurant in Baltimore by far. Service, food, hospitality is all top notch. I've been here likely 25 times in the last 10 years and it never disappoints.
Had an amazing dinner with husband. Food was delicious and large portions. All the staff were fantastic.

Exquisite dining venue tucked away in Little Italy, the food was amazing and the service was excellent. Our bus Boys always made sure our glasses were full and we had a smile on our face. We ate the restaurant week menu and were blown away! Most importantly, the olives we started off with were some of the best Olives we've ever had. So much flavor throughout the night and the canoli for dessert really sealed the deal!
Great Restaurant - Wonderful atmosphere - Great Food
We were there for restaurant week.  They had great selections for first and second courses.  Both dessert choices were excellent.  As busy as they were, the staff was attentive.

Had our company holiday party there and it was fabulous. Wine at the bar was excellent with a great bartender! Upstairs in the library, they served the 24 of us with fantastic food, kept my wine glass full, and 3 hours passed seemingly in minutes. We are stuffed and delighted. The service staff were great! We met Aldo's son while waiting for the valet to bring our car around, very nice young man, cute too! We'll be back.
Awesome atmosphere, amazing food.  The homemade pasta was perfect, and the shrimp (in the bisque appetizer) and flounder (in the special entree) were unbelievably tender. Everything was delicious!
Went for a company Christmas Party. Food was good and overall experience was great
(Translated by Google) Wonderful food and good wine.  (Original) Comida maravilhosa e bom vinho.
Amazing food.  The staff was even better. They were knowledgeable and attentive.  It was so nice to have a little history lesson about the restaurant. A must visit when in Baltimore.
Fan DAMN Tastic... best of Baltimore in any and all categories
Great food and great staff
Spectacular! In one word Spectacular!

Had a reservation at 8 and didn't get seated until 10. They offered free drinks at their bar, which had an awful beer selection and everything taste stale.  Food was meh... Save your time and money and go to olive garden.
Our favorite date night place. Great food, great service. Great for date nights and groups.

My wife and I had a very nice dinner at Aldo's this week. The food was good, Marco our waiter was very professional and the room and ambiance were wonderful. My Bronzini could have used some lemon and butter sauce and my wife was disappointed that they didn't have angel hair pasta. We will definitely return to Aldo's Restaurant.  Ray and Linda Gordon  Bel Air
Delicious
Such a special place. We found it by chance and keep going back for significant events. Just celebrated a milestone birthday and anniversary and we were so well taken care of!!

Super slow service. Took advantage of a big party to overcharge us. $70 for a house wine which was $13 in a store, $54 for a plate of a caesar salat which should be included in the pefix menu. Online they post $29 per person but charged our party $35 per person. The food was nothing special. Restaurant week price was just a way to get you in the door. We'll never be back.

AWFUL EXPERIENCE!! Came here for restaurant week with a reservation for a large party! They declined to share any pricings or share the menu and kept the party completely out of the blue! We tried to order house wine for the table and they failed to mention it was $70 for a HOUSE BOTTLE!!! Management was completely rude and unwilling to accommodate for the miscommunication with the servers. Stay away from this place!!! We will never be back.
Food is excellent, served hot. Great experience with wait staff. Going back whenever we can.
Best limoncello martini in town.
Fresh real food. Prepare to walk out feeling very full.
Elegant atmosphere, gracious service, and delicious meals!
Always incredible food and great service.
Food was amazing. Definitely will come back again.

I absolutely loved this place. My wife and I recently visited Aldo's Italain in Baltimore for our wedding anniversary weekend. I found this place online from a heap of similar Italian restaurants in the area. I'm so glad I decided on Aldo's. From when we first came in, we were greeted at the door by the friendly staff. Our waitress, Shanti, did her absolute best to make sure we we're well catered to. The food was impeccabble. I don't even like eggplant, but this eggplant I love! I'm glad I stole some of my wife's food. The gnocchi I still dream about. Most importantly, the atmosphere is wonderful! We sat in the open alcoce with the setting sun. Couldn't have asked for anything better. We loved this place so much, we ditched our after dinner plans and just sat and talked for hours. Definitely adding this place to the "revisit" list.
(Translated by Google) Very good service, fantastic food  (Original) Muy buena atención , comida fantástica
Excellent service and food
Romantic restaurant...great food
Luxurious, cozy, vegetarian friendly.
Aldos is probably the most wonderful restaurant I have been to in Baltimore. Everything is great ... ambiance, staff, service  and, especially the food!!!

Very disappointed. I was looking forward to trying the food here but last night after being seated at the table I was not greeted by anyone at all. After about 15 minutes I informed a hostess and she sent the server over. Once the server came over he seem frazzled and didn’t even ask what we wanted to drink. He then disappeared and was helping tables around us but not even acknowledging me and my boyfriend. Another 10-15 minutes went by and we just walked out. I am so incredibly disappointed and this is not fine dining quality service.
Best Italian in Baltimore. Exquisite service!
Rude

Elegant ambiance and good food. Some dishes were outstanding, some just average. Veal saltimbocca needed salt (not available on the table). Very good branzino and wild boar pappardelle specials. Chocolate mousse was pedestrian and "rustic apple tart" (a mini tarte tatin) was doughy. A nice wine and an after-dinner drink rounded out a nice evening.
Great atmosphere, pleasant staff and excellent food.
For authentic Italian food...you can not go wrong. Excellent atmosphere. Great service. Pricey but worth it. Treat yourself to an elegant and special evening.

It was my first  time visiting Baltimore and my company treated our team to an amazing dinner!  The evening began in their cozy bar area with a celebratory cocktail and some incredible wine! We were then escorted to a private room for our team dinner which was just the perfect size. We started with some appetizers and I would definitely recommend the gluten free meatballs and the eggplant. Our entrees were delicious and some of the best veal francais I have ever had.  We complimented our superb dinners with several mouthwatering desserts and I would recommend the tiramisu, cannolis and of course the homemade lemoncello. I can’t wait to go back and try another amazing dish and sip on some outstanding wine. One of the best Italian restaurants I have ever visited.

I attended a business dinner at Aldo's last night. It was absolutely one of the finest dining experience I've ever had. Service was outstanding and friendly (like family) and the food & wine was amazing. I'd never had wild boar before and it was great!
Absolutely phenomenal! Food, drinks, and service were beyond fantastic! Highly recommend!
My husband and I loved Aldo's. The food was spectacular, atmosphere was lovely. This place is now in my top 3 for authentic Italian. We will definitely return.
Service was great, but pasta was overcooked.  For all the great reviews I was not overly impressed.
Excellent food and service.
Great Italian as expected but also a mega crab cake.
Everything was great   Ossobucco, Fois Gras, and flourless chocolate cake.
Great food!
Always great. What else can I say
The brunch was very good.  Captain Crunch French toast, what?!
Great date night. Limited vegan options, but enough to get by and pretty tasty, too.
Food was very good. Exactly what you expect for the price.
Had a wonderful meal. Food was top notch, service was great. We all had a superb time.
Cosy place with good enough food.
Dining in Aldo' s is always a great experience. Food quality, decent portions, and the atmosphere is so relaxing.
Great food and service! Wonderful Valentine's Day dinner!
I went on New Year's eve and was blown away. I will be back.
Great restaurant. Food is delicious and the staff is professional and attentive to every detail. Highly recommend!
BEST IN BALTIMORE!
Outstanding
Amazing building and decoration. There was no music playing so it was very quite. I didn't want others to hear my conversation. I would have loved to see more seafood. My noodles were great!
Great food and atmosphere
Good food, great atmosphere, and excellent service

Meal was excellent, as always. Had the Eggplant Parmesan for appetizers, the Wild Boar Ragu as supplemental dish and the Tagliata di Manso ( Tuscan style steak). Everything wad prepared perfectly. My server David was attentive to my needs during my visit. Margaret in the bar was a "GEM " when I stopped in there for an after dinner drink. Her suggestion of the Grappa was spot on. She was very pleasant and thoughtful. The best dining in Little Italy.

The quiet side rooms are great for business next time I'll get the wine room. Perfect restaurant not large "dining hall" feeling. Service was good , parking easy and I had the crab cakes. I would normally not order crab cakes at an Italian Restaurant but the server suggested them. Great choice.

Wonderful place and great food. Picked it specifically for a date night with the wife expecting it to be quiet and romantic, but was a bit disappointed. Tables were really close together and there were a few noisy tables. The food was good though.
Really good food.

Awful experience and food. They publicized a special Christmas Eve dinner. We made reservations. We were seated in the bar because our table wasn’t ready. Fine, but it took more than half an hour before we were seated. Then another half hour before we could order. We ordered from the special menu thinking that’s what they were best prepared to do. When the pastas came they were so over cooked they were mushy. I had to spit out my braised calamari because it was so fishy tasting. The tab was over $400 with wine and 2 cocktails. Terrible food, bad service.

My dad started coming to Aldo’s many years ago during business trips to town. Fast forward and for the last 7 years I lived in Baltimore for work and my weekly dinner regiment includes Aldo’s. Everything is quite literally perfect. From the food to the staff to the decor to the valet parking each night. Outstanding choice and one that delivers perfection over and over again. I highly recommend Aldo’s in Baltimore’s Little Italy and will continue to dine with them for the foreseeable future! If I could give six stars, I would! I believe they’re also the only restaurant that’s accessible which is just another reason they’re so amazing!

Amazing ambiance and meal.  The place is amazing. The staff is very polite and the service was fast. Ordered the shrimp scampi which was really good. It was only 3 shrimp on top of garlic bread but it was mouth watering. I had the Aldo's Signiture filet mignon which was melt in your mouth goodness. The wife had a pasta which she didn't like, but I did, so will be taking to work the next morning. Ordered the tiramisu for desert and that was also, you guessed it, amazing. Would highly recommend this place for date night.  My only 2 complaints would be the portion size. I know these high end places usually serve smaller portions, but I'm so used to having larger portions and definitely wanted more of that filet. The 2nd complaint would be th dress code. I thought this place was suits and dresses. Not the case. There was a group in there that had on football jerseys hoodies.  All in all was a great experience!

Food was ok to good, service was very attentive. Prices were out of control ridiculous. We had 7 people and ended up with a bill of over 700$ they also add gratuity to the bill and don't tell you. I HATE that. Thankfully we noticed.
Delightful old-school Italian eatery with DELICIOUS house-made, complimentary limoncello. Waiter was a charm!
Best Italian restaurant in Baltimore. Carpaccio is out of this world. Wild boar Bolognese sometimes on menu. Get it. Classy ambiance. Impeccable service.
Really great food. And even better service. They also do items of the menu based on your requests and what they have in the kitchen.
Consistently excellent. Our favorite in Baltimore.
Nice small restaurant. Service is very good. Fantastic pasta.  Salads are good.
Impeccable food and fantastic atmosphere!
Great atmosphere. Excellent food. Superior customer service.

The waiters were extremely great. The transition time between appetizer , main course and desert was perfect. I particularly loved their eggplant appetizer. Their price is a little on the high side, but a great place to break your bank ones in a while.

This is THE place for Italian food in Baltimore. Frankly, it could very well be the finest restaurant in the city. Staff is professional and kind. Dining rooms and bar and restrooms are impeccably clean. Fancy bathroom hand towels. (Gotta love it.) White tablecloth. Good music. Quaint neighborhood (Little Italy). Can't say enough good about the owners!!! And the menu is just full of winners. Every salad, appetizer, soup, entree, dessert...all delicious. Run, don't walk. ;-)
Victor was a most genial host. Calamari was the best ever. Main courses delightful and desserts sinful. Wait staff very accommodating. Made for a wonderful anniversary dinner.
Service was good.. Food Good ..
Went there to celebrate my birthday and it was one of the best experience I have had at a  Baltimore dining establishment

Food was pretty decent, unfortunately my date got sick later that evening from her dinner and threw it all back up :/ . The service at first was prompt and responsive. However after receiving the drinks and appetizers it was a very long time in between receiving the meals we both ordered. The plates lacked and sides and for an entree one would expect that, nope just fish and sides extra. The prices are high, the portions are small. Also during the stay the lights seemed to go on and off at their leisure like it was a signal it was time to go. It was ending the evening, dinner reservations were at 930 pm. Don't think we will be returning, unfortunate because the reviews I read were all positive. Hope you have better luck.
I know that it's one of the busiest restaurant nights of the year, but when I have a reservation for 8pm and you haven't seated all of your 7pm reservations yet, there's a problem.

Long wait time, even though I had a reservation. Food was salty. They were very crowded and crammed too many people into the dinning rooms. I went there for Valentine's Day and it was anything but romantic. I wouldn't go there again.
The service was great but the food was not as good as I would have hoped for, especially for the price.
On the expensive side but worth every penny. Excellent service and excellent food, prepared to perfection. Not your mother's "Little Italy" restaurant.

Made this our choice for a birthday dinner. Got there a bit early before our reservations but were seated right away. Service was great and kept coming from all angles. Food was awesome as well. We left full and content.

Amazing place to dine. Of course the price to eat here will be high because it is made at a high quality. I recommend to anyone looking for something new to try this place. It works great for business meetings and romantic dining.
ok italian food. expected more impact from flavor in the dishes considering the good reviews Aldo's receives.
They had really good food and the level of service was awesome too
Hands down one of the best restaurant experiences I've ever had. The food is exquisite, artfully presented, and the service outstanding. A must visit place when you're in Baltimore.

Food and service was excellent.  Beef carpaccio, buratta and trio is pasta.  Each of the three pastas were really fresh and sauces  were great.  Bolognese, orrechietta with sausage and carbonara.  Nick our waiter was super.  Thanks for a great dinner.
My wife and I had the most.spectacular dinner with a great waiter and a delicious wine. Cannot say enough great things about our experience.
The minestrone soup was delicious!

Outstanding establishment.  From beginning to end we  had an outstanding meal and with outstanding service.  Would recommend Aldo's to anyone looking for an unforgettable dining experience for any occasion.

I live in Annapolis and drive 30 miles when I want an Italian dinner. When I do I dinr at Aldo's. The staff is knowledgable and attentive. The food is excellent. Plenty of parking within a few blocks or you can use valet. Aldo is a warm, gracious host and attentive to his clientele. Opinions will differ and I won't claim you will share my opinion but I make the drive everytime so I at least have the courage of my convictions.

Housemade LEMONCELLO!!!! (Oprah Voice) amazing!!!!! Carbonara is the best I've ever had!!!!!! Eggplant Parmesan is nuts!!!!! Don't hesitate!!!!! And the Beef Carpaccio......... I'm shaking my head writing this, so delicious!!!!!! I always sit at the bar because Margret is amazing, but the dinning room looks elegant!!!
Food was good but not special.

My husband brought me for our anniversary and it was an amazing experience. It's class is higher than our lifestyle so for special events it is great to experience and the food was all amazing and tasty. Our server was very helpful and knowledgeable about the menu even brought us a few gifts to taste.
A+ food and service
ABSOLUTELY LOVELY 👉👌

Simple and elegant setting. Superb staff, Nick took excellent care of my wife and I, it was best service we've ever had. It is pricy but neither food quality or quantity is neglected. Everything tastes amazing and it's the reason the restaurant has been around for twenty years. For a truly fantastic dinner this is the place to go.
Quite possibly the best dining experience in Baltimore. The food is delicious and the atmosphere is A+! Don't forget to order the LIMONCELLO!! it is the best!

This was my first time at Aldo's and it was an absolutely fantastic experience. The service was incredible and the food was the best Italian food that I've had in the city (clam linguini, bolognese, lobster fettuccine, tiramisu). Allesandro and his staff made us feel very much like family and this restaurant deserves much more than 5 stars. Looking forward to going back!

We had a combined 40th and 90th birthday party in one of Aldo's private rooms on a Saturday night. The food and atmosphere, as always, were out of this world and the service was impeccable. Great place to have a large event!

We were blown away by quality of food and the old school charm.  Wonderfully prepared Italian menu, as good as anything NYC can offer in our experience. The perfect combination of refined cuisine and home style Callabrian cooking. Chefs Aldo Vitale and Sergio Vitale man the kitchen and made time to personally visit with us to see how we enjoyed the meal. Aldo kindly ended the meal with a surprise delicacy he made after hearing about our recent trip to Rome, and then topped things off with a complimentary home made Lemoncello. We were treated like family. This is a not-to-miss experience.
As usual, another great experience at Aldo's.  I don't know what is better, the food or the service.

The ambiance is wonderful.  The service is outstanding.  And the food is exquisite. I've never had anything at Aldo's that wasn't incredible.  Spaghettoni alla Carbonara is my favorite pasta dish and Aldo's makes the best!  And don't leave without trying their homemade Limoncello.
Simply Awesome!!!
We had a wonderful evening, well taken care of, great food, beautiful space.  Love the tuxedos! Thanks Aldo's staff
Went for dinner tonight with my friend and everything was great and on point completely delicious food

Great Restaurant !! Service was awesome I was with a wounded warrior and the ADA access was easy and the staff went out of their way to show their appreciation!  We have been to Aldo's before and we will be back! GO ARMY!! We found out Aldo served in U.S. Army and was drafted for Nam!!

Aldo's is by far the best restaurant in Little Italy. From the top notch service to the amazing cuisine, you won't be disappointed. Even if you are only looking for a glass of wine, Margaret, will lead you in the right direction. I have frequented Little Italy my entire life & no restaurant has matched my experiences at Aldo's.

Aldo's has authentic Italian cuisine and is just as delicious as I have had while in Italy!  Its beautiful interior and the excellent staff make your experience there even more special.  I'd recommend this to everyone who appreciates great food!

Best food in Baltimore bar none. My go-to place for special occasions or just as a treat. Been a customer for 10+ years and have been probably 25 times total. Never a bad meal or service. Always top notch. Well worth it
The Tuna TarTar and Carbonara was great. So was the service and the valet. However, I prefer Grano Emporio in Hampden. Nice stroll if staying around inner harbor.

I had made reservations for an early dinner at 5pm on a Saturday evening. We arrived on time and after a brief wait, were promptly seated at our table. The hostess was polite, professional, and greeted us with warm smiles when we had initially walked in. That's about the extent of the pleasantness of the dining experience. The bread we were served was cold (perhaps this is normal here - I cannot comment on that), the wait staff inattentive (we waited 20+ minutes to have our card run; we also seldom saw our wait staff), and the main course portion sizes were a bit dismal. On the plus side, the location was good, the food quality was high, and the ambiance was perfect. For my first and only visit, I am rating this place as "Okay."
phenomenal food

Been there twice in one week.  First time was on a Saturday evening and our experience was great - I give it four stars.  The second time was a Sunday evening and our experience was only a two star.  Both times we ordered the the lamb chops and Aldo special "Ossobuco" as well as the sauteed wild mushrooms.  First time they were great second time they weren't. The main courses were either burnt, cold and tasteless; the mushrooms were dried out and looked like they had been sitting out for a while. We had the same experience with the service. Saturday was great and Sunday was so so.  So what's the moral to this review?  Don't go on Sunday as there must be a different chef.  Finally, we did try the calamari appetizer and it was great - very light and fresh.

Waited 30 min. before being seated. The bar made a great amaretto sour and vodka soda. We had bread to snack while we waited. Total dining time was 2:45, too long. The waiter came up to us 3 times during the whole meal. My flank steak dish was cold and the carbonara was lacking flavor. Excuses were "A big party just left" and "We are understaffed." Pros: Food was tasty, but cold, drinks were spot on, great decor, good location in Little Italy Cons: Poor service by waiter, check ins, cold food etc. Made no offer to compensate for the bad dining experience.

I've eaten at Aldo's for 5 years now and every time I go I am never disappointed.  The menu is constantly kept up to date with fresh ingredients dependent on the season which always is a great taste to have!  The wine selection cannot be beat.  Aldo himself is such a friendly person too!  I see him at the bar sometimes and go to say hello and thank him for such a wonderful meal.  Love the place and absolutely recommend it.
Sublime, wonderful, the food was a dance in my mouth! The service was perfect and we had an amazing inventive meal! The best!

When we arrived there at 7:00pm last night, we were told there was a 30-45 minute wait so we decided to wait. Between 7:45 and 8:00 we were seated downstairs. In about 10 minutes the waiter came out to take our order. Our food arrived around 9:15.  The staff was friendly, and the ambience was lovely, though it felt like we were in a cellar of someones old house. The food was also very good.  The only thing that made this a bad experience was the wait time. I was on a company trip and we hoped to do some sightseeing before turning in for the night which was now not possible. With how expensive the meals were, I would have expected faster service. They didnt even apologize for the wait time.  I went to Zagat (because they had a Zagat award at their front door) to place a review but it doesnt allow you to place a review and so theres no way to let them know about the experience. Made me wonder if Zagat is getting paid for their stellar reviews only.

We made reservations at Aldo's for April 12, 2013 to celebrate my Mother in law's 90th Birthday and we worked with Margaret, the Private dining Coordinator to organize our activity. We had the Library Room. Everything from the moment we arrived to our leaving was handled magnificently. The service received by the waiters attending our dinner was Outstanding. They named one of the cocktails the Rose Bellini and it was super. There was great flexibility in the menu offered to our group and every item served was wonderful, specially the Ossobucco, Chicken, Shrimp Scampi and Veal Saltimbocca that most attendees ordered.We had a delicious crispy eggplant parmigiana for 2nd course that was out of this world after our cold antipasto dishes that we shared and our salad of mixed greens was wonderful.  We brought our own cake and they served it for us. All attendees raved about their entrees and specially our family from NY, used to very good italian Restaurants.  The Library Room was the perfect choice allowing privacy and space and comfort for our activity since we had italian music played and a video- slide presentation. And at the end when we are coming down, my Mother in Law was the star with a good number of customers congratulating her and wishing her well. With absolutely no doubt I consider Aldo's the Best Italian Restaurant in all of Maryland. And will continue to do business with them. THANKS Aldo's!

Phenomenal food service and atmosphere. I have never been to an Italian restaurant this nice. You definitely pay for it but it is well worth it. The waiters all wear tuxes, and the deserts are out of this world
Great service and attention to detail.  The food was good and they make their own gluten free pasta!
